dialog.label: Create Job Plan from Work Plan

helpgrid.innerhtml: Enter a job plan number or generate one by clicking Autonumber. Click OK to create the Job Plan.

Enter the details for your optimization server. If you run optimization on-premise, enter the URL of the optimization server and the optimization model repository information. Each optimization model listed must have its own user name and password in the Optimization Model. If you run optimization on the cloud, select the optimization model and click Deploy.
You must create one new user in the database for each optimization model. The user and its associated schema cannot be used for any other purpose.

dialog.label: Configure Gantt View Properties: User Settings

helpgrid.innerhtml: Specify the properties to display in the data table of the Gantt view. The settings will affect the current schedule.
Define the relationship between the work records, which will determine the scheduling order.
Define the variables that you want the optimization model to take into account when leveling resources. The template can be used to optimize any schedule.
To find a crew that is available during a specific date range, enter the dates in the From and To fields. To include crews who are already assigned to other jobs, select Include Fully Assigned.
To find labor available during a specific date range, enter the dates in the From and To fields. To include labor who are already assigned to other jobs, select Include Fully Assigned.
